                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3003: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-03T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 3, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 3—5:30
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1037. Department’s 443, November 30, 11 a.m. Following telephone message from
                    Colonel Margetts this morning: <pb facs="0727" n="617" xml:id="pg_617"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Lieutenant Aldrich reached Liao River yesterday and reports all Japanese
                            forces have been transferred east of the river, except 300 for guard
                            duty at Hsinmin and to patrol railway between Hsinmin and Paikipu. It is
                            expected that the railway between Tahushan and Hsinmin will be repaired
                            by the Chinese today or tomorrow. Aldrich returns to Chinchow
                            today.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
